        {
          "username": "Michelle L (Michelle)",
          "rating": 2,
          "contributor_id": "106349883665488333591",
          "user_review_count": 41,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwMGrNIxjCsrQuEsH5Y7VTYaHAmLDobmJbc5RjhukdmB1J2w4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I suggest avoiding this location on Fridays between 12 noon - 3pm, they have a walk-in clinic where the line is out the door. The staff are overwhelmed and not focused. It was mayhem in their office. My appt. Was rescheduled from noon to 1pm, without my consent. When I inquired, they apologized. I showed up for my urgent care appt. and the staff, very compassionate and kind, also very young and inexperienced. As I was talking to the nurse practitioner, we were interrupted every 1-2 min. the other staff were knocking on the door, entering and asking non-urgent questioned like \u201cwhere\u2019s the whiteout?\u201d At times I was being examined and that occurred. It\u2019s not quality healthcare when a patient cannot have privacy and speak about one\u2019s health without distraction. Other offices would have suggested blood work, and when I asked about why she was prescribing an antibiotic prior to confirming if it\u2019s necessary, she told me, it\u2019s just in case - the testing isn\u2019t up to standards. I have had really great health care in the past and this was alarming. They scheduled an automatic appt. Without asking me. It\u2019s a very unorganized office, and in an urgent care situation, I\u2019m sorry but I can\u2019t deal with all that randomness. That\u2019s not helpful.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KS2JqRjRYekl5VkVWbFQwSldjVUpKYjJGc1FrRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x4e4b88bc80833369!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmJKbjF4XzIyVEVlT0JWcUJJb2FsQkE%7C%7C?hl=en",
